{
  "texts": [
    "The simulation results of all algorithms are obtained using 30 search agents with 1000 iterations and 10 independent runs.",
    "Table 7 shows that the BKA algorithm outperformed the other eight algorithms by achieving 8 out of the 12 test functions with the best results, or 66.7% of the total.",
    "Figure 12 shows that the results of BKA, GJO, PSO, and AVOA perform well on F1, but all have outliers, indicating that the performance of these algorithms is relatively high but not stable enough.",
    "Other algorithms perform very well in functions F2 and F6 except for SSA.",
    "In Fig. 13, it can be seen that BKA performs stably on all functions, proving that BKA is robust."
  ]
}